title: Bug 121170 - getColumnLabel() returns null labels before extraction and recognizable strings after extraction
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction, the labels returned are null. However, after the data has been extracted, the labels are recognizable strings.
EB: The expected behavior is for IMetaData.getColumnLabel() to return recognizable strings even before data extraction.
SR: To reproduce the issue, call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction and observe the returned labels. Then, extract the data and call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() again to compare the labels before and after extraction.
